Skeptics say the slightly higher returns aren't enough to compensate for the extra risk.They warn that asset-backed securities are only as good as the assets and credit backing that support them -- and those are hard to evaluate.Moreover, the securities were introduced only about 4 1/2 years ago; the biggest unknown is how they will fare in a recession.Such concerns haven't stopped asset-backed securities from becoming one of Wall Street's hottest new products
