Options traders were hurt worse than others on Friday because of the highly volatile nature of options, which often rise or fall in value several times the amount of the price change in the individual stock or index of stocks on which they are based.Thus, options traders Friday were stuck with losses that also were several times larger than those suffered by many stock traders in New York
